				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Zombie Army: The bloody card game" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The goal as the name suggests is to form the largest army of zombies as possible, attacking your enemies and &amp;quot;zombifying&amp;quot; them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;First, each player must pick a card in the package identified as HUMAN, this is an open card depicting their character to start the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Then, players are distributed a package of 7 ACTION cards each. These are the cards that will enable them to attack or defend themselves against their opponents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Zombie Army, the player that is attacked by a zombie is considered out after three strikes, same as Baseball.&amp;#10;So in order to make a human become a zombie: &amp;#10;Zombie attack: Strike one&amp;#10;Neck, arm or leg bite: Strike two&amp;#10;Human infected: Strike tree, you're dead&amp;#10; In turn, clockwise, players must attack their opponents using strategy and luck in order to &amp;quot;zombify&amp;quot; the characters of their opponents and take possession of them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the player who has the most HUMAN cards in their army.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is extremely simple to play based on the principle of action reaction, it is &amp;quot;addictive&amp;quot;. It combines strategy, luck, scheming and friendship and it is easy to carry and play everywhere. No board game, no dice, no pieces, no calculation or complicated numbers, only cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
